The "Application Launcher" subsystem provides background synchronization of AGContacts databases with system databases, as well as processing various system events (new calls in the call log, adding and changing contacts, etc.). Its operation requires notification in the Notification Panel, which may contain additional services (optional display of the Call Statistics widget, Quick Call widgets, and quick launch buttons of the program).

If you do not need additional features of the "Application Launcher" subsystem, you can hide this notification by turning off the display of notifications in the application launcher notification channel settings, or lower their importance by disabling the notification on the Lock Screen, turning off the icon in the Status Bar, etc. You can also always change this in the program settings in the "Performance" subsection and in the settings of the "Application Launcher" subsystem itself, accessible from the notification.

Entering a phone number:
1. To enter a phone number manually - use the dialpad buttons.
2. To enter the symbol + - use a long press of the button \"0\".
3. To paste a phone number from the clipboard or copy it to the clipboard - use the context menu over the dialing field.
4. To erase the last typed character - use the erase button.
5. To erase all dialed characters - use a long press of the erase button.
6. To insert a selected contact phone number in the dialing field - click on its name or number in the dialing field.
7. To select phone number of contact from the lists - click on the desired contact or phone number in the lists.
Sending a calls:
1. To send a call - use the call button.
2. If in the dialing field displays information about the selected contact from the lists - press the call button sends the call to this the selected number of contact.
3. To send a call to the manually entered phone number - in this case, use a long press of the call button.
4. To disable automatic selection of the contact\'s phone number from the lists - disable the option \"Direct call\" (Menu -> \"Initial setting\") or use the settings section \"Direct call\" ( \"Settings\" -> \"Calls\").
5. To call your voice mail - use a long press of the button \"1\" (if voice mail is set up in the system and is available for the call).
6. Speed ​​Dial - use a long-pressing the buttons \"2\"-\"9\".
Other actions:
1. To enter the mode Full-text searching - use a long press of the button \"*\" (the magnifying glass icon on the right).
2. To enter the mode Voice dialing and searching - use the button with the microphone icon or long press the button \"#\" (the microphone icon on the right).
3. If the microphone icon is not displayed and voice input is not activated - install the Google app from Google Play and then restart the phone.
4. To minimize/maximize the dialpad - use gestures up/down on it or click on the dialing field or on a slider above it.
Important related settings:
1. To adjust the behavior, location of on-screen or signature of buttons - use the settings section \"Dialpad\" (\"Settings\" -> \"User interface\").
2. To set up the fonts and heights of the dialpad buttons - use the settings section \"Dialpad\" ( \"Settings\" -> \"Theme\" -> \"Customize current theme\" -> \"Dialpad\").
3. To set up the colors and background - use the settings sections \"Basic colors\" and \"Base backgrounds\" ( \"Settings\" -> \"Theme\" -> \"Customize current theme\").
4. To adjust the logic of calls - use settings sections \"Calls\" and \"Dual SIM support\" (for devices with 2 and 3 SIM-cards).

Enter the Mask for parsing phone numbers with the required mask symbols (*#N), special characters and digits of the number (+/N/*/#,;0..9) and without format symbols (-./()␣):

Mask symbols:
* - a group of zero, one or several any digits of the number
# - one any digit of the number
N - one any special character or digit of the number

Special characters and digits:
+ - character \'+\' (plus)
/N - character \'N\' (latin N)
/* - character \'*\' (asterisk)
/# - character \'#\' (pound)
, - character \',\' (comma - pause)
; - character \';\' (semicolon - wait)
0..9 - characters \'0\'..\'9\' (digits)

Examples:
8* or #######

Special characters and digits:

, - character \',\' (comma - pause)

Format symbols:
( and ) - symbols \'(\' and \')\' (parentheses)
- - symbol \'-\' (dash)
. - symbol \'.\' (dot)
/ - symbol \'/\' (slash)

Format:
*0#*n#Number?Name

1. *0# - optional, force "Confirm before call"
2. *n# - optional, n=1/2 - SIM-card number
3. Number - number to call or USSD-request
4. ?Name - optional, text (must start with "?")

Examples:
1. +7-(953)-111-22-33 - call to +79531112233
2. *2#*100#?Balans - call to *100# over SIM2

The subsystem is intended for short presentation of the basic features and settings of a particular function of the program or its subsystems. Displayed upon first use of relevant function of the program as long as the hints is not marked as read. Subsystem is a pop-up window with a timer to auto-hide.
Use subsystem:
1. To mark all displayed tips as readed - use the button \"Mark all as read\" (double check mark on the left top).
2. To lock auto-hide the window - use the button \"Lock auto-hide\" (padlock on the top right).
3. To force close the window - use the button \"Close window\" (cross on the top right).
4. To mark one tip as readed - use its the button \"Mark as read\" (checkmark to the right).
To display all of the tips:
